ArcelorMittal Kazakh Unit to Spend $915 Million to Boost Output

-- B y   N a r i m a n   G i z i t d i n o v
-- 
2011-02-16T06:49:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-16/arcelormittal-kazakh-unit-to-spend-915-million-to-boost-output.html
  ArcelorMittal ’s Kazakh unit will
spend 134 billion tenge ($915 million) to boost steel output 50
percent by 2015, the government said.  ArcelorMittal Temirtau agreed on the plan with the
government in December, Vice Prime Minister Aset Isekeshev told
a cabinet meeting in Astana today in a broadcast posted on the
government’s website.  The unit of the world’s biggest steelmaker said Feb. 8 that
it plans to increase production by 20 percent to 4 million
metric tons of liquid steel this year and to 6 million tons by
2015.  Natalya Vysotskaya, a spokeswoman for ArcelorMittal
Temirtau, declined to make an immediate comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nariman Gizitdinov in Almaty at 
 ngizitdinov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at 
 sev@bloomberg.net  